criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Male or female, 18 to 70 years of age;

          2. Chronic (e.g., duration of injury at least 6 months), stable SCI (regardless of level
             of lesion or completeness of injury);

          3. Concurrently participating in or previously completed protocol # 0454-06-073, "Risk
             Factors for Coronary Heart Disease in Spinal Cord Injury: conventional and emerging".

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Acute medical illness;

          2. Pregnancy (as determined by a pregnancy test < 1 week of the study); and

          3. The presence of a chronic disease (i.e., heart disease, pulmonary disease, etc.);

          4. Inability to comply with breathing instructions.
